OL,5, Children face a "postcode lottery" when
OL,6, it comes to the quality of school      
OL,7, meals, according to a campaigner.      
OL,9,FIt comes after a head teacher in       
OL,10,FSouthampton blamed the "completely     
OL,11,Funacceptable" food served in his       
OL,12,Fcanteen on a private catering company. 
OL,14,FAward-winning food campaigner Saffron  
OL,15,FStedall said: "It's heart-breaking to  
OL,16,Fsee the differences between schools."  
OL,18,FThe Department for Education (DfE) said
OL,19,Fschools must work with suppliers to    
OL,20,F"ensure high standards are in place".  
